race.comment: RAPIDO RIVER (8) has had a few chances but looks well placed off a good effort last start at Cranbourne, finding the line strongly over 2025m to grab third. She's never raced over this trip but looks to be crying out for it off the last run and any improvement sees her go close. NICOFFHOME (4) is knocking on the door with four minor placings in a row, okay in a small field at Bendigo last time in what looked a stronger maiden. He'll land on speed and give a sight. HARD GRUNT (3) was no match for an easy winner at Echuca last time but stuck on well for second and should have no issue rising in trip now. CULTURAL ATTACHE (2) has been well beaten in two runs to date but is open to plenty of improvement while I'MFALLINFORYOU (7) is going well and can prove hard to hold out.
